text: I don t know who else to talk to  but for the first time ever I ve actually thought about suicide For the past   years I ve been as strong as I could and truly believed that I d be happy with my life at one point   I have a lot of support from my family and I m even talking to a therapist right now but I feel like I m lying to myself every time I talk to him  I ll be very motivated and encouraged but then I ll get lonely and I go back to focusing on everything that s wrong  Besides my personal life  everything about this world is so incredibly fucked up and hopeless to me  It s the biggest struggle and the only advice I get is pretty much  that s life  I know it is  I know it s not fair and I know it s up to me to accept it but I can t  I m tired of getting up and pretending to be okay  I m tired of giving my all to people who don t do the same  I m tired of feeling bad about myself  I m tired of not being able to help others  I m tired of feeling like life has no meaning  I want to cry all the time  and this week has been absolute shit to me  I broke up with my boyfriend  I found out one my coworkers  who I was pretty close to  was murdered  my mom listened in on my therapy and started making me feel like shit  I have no really good close friends in my city and although my family loves me  I truly don t feel like anyone understands the unbearable pain I feel all the time  I m terrified of my own thoughts right now but I m also scared if I tell my therapist he ll tell my family and they ll make me go to a psych ward  I ve always been too scared and say I would never because I don t want to make my family go through that pain but I m at a point where I don t want to be here anymore because no matter how hard I try  something new comes up  If anyone has any guidance or words that might help I appreciate it
